- The energy consumption data is collected daily and aggregated to determine the rankings;
- The rankings are based on the total energy consumption, average maximum load, and average minimum load;
- The query also considers the region's name and the customer's ID to provide context.

- The "average maximum load" refers to the average of the highest energy consumption values in kilowatts (kW) for each region;
- The "overall average maximum load" is the average of the highest energy consumption values across all regions;
- The "number of customers" refers to the distinct count of customers in each region.

- 'sunny' refers to weather conditions that are clear and without clouds;
- 'smart meter' is a type of data source that measures energy consumption in real-time;
- 'MV' stands for megavolts, a unit of energy consumption;
- 'kW' stands for kilowatts, a unit of power.

