- 'energy savings goal' indicates that the customer has a specific target for reducing energy consumption;
- 'maximum load' is measured in kilowatts (kW) and represents the highest energy consumption recorded for a customer during the specified weather conditions.

- "peak energy demand" refers to the maximum load in kilowatts (kW);
- "average energy consumption" is the average energy consumption in megavolts (MV);
